title: Design the logo for a unique automotive streetwear brand...
description: Automotive lifestyle/streetwear clothing brand based on the mantra that "it is more fun to drive a slow-car fast than to drive a fast-car slow." Sure being able to tell people your car has 600 horsepower is cool, but unless your on a racetrack, where are you ever going to be able to safely/legally use any of those ponies? In the automotive space, merchandise is always about being the fastest or having the most power. It also tends to be cheesy, cliche, and predictable. slowcarfast looks to target a different audience. In essence, it is a clothing brand for people who on the one hand care about fashion, and on the other hand love cars, but don't take themselves too seriously. They drive for the experience, they believe that how a car handles is more important that straight-line speed, and they understand that fun is better than fast. They know they aren't winning any drag races and they are ok with that - they aren't pretending to be something they are not. And they want to look good all the while.
other_notes:
I’m interested in wordmark, and abstract logos. Take a look at the references I provided (more than the "design inspiration" logos they gave to choose from). The references represent the kind of clean streetwear style logo I kind of have in mind.
I get it, slowcarfast is kind of abstract and the words would initially cause one to think that the logo must involve a car, or tires, etc., but that is not really what I am looking for. I’ve received some logos and some of them weren’t bad but that being said, I’m very open to the unpredictable. Attention grabbing visuals as long as they’re well done. I have a deep appreciation for the off-beat and abstract - again, as long as they’re done well and they ride that line between playfull yet professional. That being said, I am not a fan of cliche or on the nose logos. Like EVERY real estate related logo having a roof on it, I would like to stay away from car silhouettes, and tires, for example. That is too predictable. Other than that, the only real requirement is that "slowcarfast" be all one word and I think I prefer it all lowercase, but you might change my mind. If you have an absurd idea… even if it doesn't match the words slowcarfast, bring the madness.
I’m totally serious. The money is guaranteed in this contest. If we end up with a strategically safe logo for slowcarfast, that’s fine. But I’m hoping for one that people see and think, what the heck is slowcarfast?!” I want it to be something that would make even non car enthusiasts want to wear it if seen on a t-shirt or a hat. This is your chance to prove that you are able to think outside of the box and design a clean/cool logo that will represent the company going forward. Just remember, this is a streetwear brand.
